1
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:06,988
QUEEN OF TEARS

2
00:01:07,947 --> 00:01:10,116
FOUR YEARS AGO

3
00:01:19,292 --> 00:01:21,044
That's strange.

4
00:01:21,669 --> 00:01:22,504
What is?

5
00:01:22,587 --> 00:01:24,130
They said this was

6
00:01:24,839 --> 00:01:26,758
the best dating spot,

7
00:01:27,509 --> 00:01:29,052
but why is it so empty?

8
00:01:31,846 --> 00:01:32,931
You're right. It is.

9
00:01:39,813 --> 00:01:41,564
RENTED FOR THE DAY

10
00:02:02,627 --> 00:02:04,337
The music…

11
00:02:05,672 --> 00:02:06,714
What about it?

12
00:02:06,798 --> 00:02:09,259
Don't they normally play

13
00:02:09,342 --> 00:02:11,636
happy songs like the ones

14
00:02:11,719 --> 00:02:13,972
in The Little Mermaid?

15
00:02:14,055 --> 00:02:16,224
It sounds a bit too romantic.

16
00:02:26,276 --> 00:02:27,152
Change the song!

17
00:02:27,235 --> 00:02:28,194
I'm sorry.

18
00:02:28,278 --> 00:02:30,780
This playlist was called "Call For Love."

19
00:02:34,617 --> 00:02:35,743
The music changed.

20
00:02:37,162 --> 00:02:38,204
You're right.

21
00:02:39,330 --> 00:02:40,290
How fascinating.

22
00:02:42,458 --> 00:02:44,669
Ms. Hong, these days

23
00:02:44,752 --> 00:02:47,172
it feels like the entire universe

24
00:02:47,797 --> 00:02:50,175
is on our side.

25
00:02:51,301 --> 00:02:54,971
We went to a famous restaurant,
and we were the only ones there.

26
00:02:55,889 --> 00:02:57,974
When we went to the amusement park,

27
00:02:58,057 --> 00:02:59,809
no one else was in that huge place

28
00:02:59,893 --> 00:03:01,686
except for us.

29
00:03:04,147 --> 00:03:05,106
You're right.

30
00:03:13,198 --> 00:03:14,407
Speaking of which…

31
00:03:15,575 --> 00:03:18,494
Since the universe is on our side…

32
00:03:21,664 --> 00:03:22,582
Will you…

33
00:03:25,001 --> 00:03:25,877
marry me?

34
00:04:40,410 --> 00:04:41,244
Are you crying?

35
00:04:45,415 --> 00:04:46,249
I'm sorry.

36
00:04:49,627 --> 00:04:51,087
About what?

37
00:05:00,013 --> 00:05:01,180
Are you that worried?

38
00:05:06,894 --> 00:05:08,187
Don't you worry.

39
00:05:14,527 --> 00:05:15,486
Baek Hyun-woo.

40
00:05:18,406 --> 00:05:19,240
I love you.

41
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,563
I wish…

42
00:05:52,982 --> 00:05:54,734
this moment wouldn't end.

43
00:05:56,569 --> 00:05:58,654
I wish you'd continue

44
00:05:59,655 --> 00:06:01,532
to smile at me

45
00:06:03,743 --> 00:06:05,411
without knowing the truth.

46
00:06:05,495 --> 00:06:07,121
What do you mean?

47
00:06:07,830 --> 00:06:08,873
What don't I know?

48
00:06:15,963 --> 00:06:17,256
Don't be shocked.

49
00:06:24,847 --> 00:06:26,474
We already went to Germany.

50
00:06:36,234 --> 00:06:37,318
We did?

51
00:06:40,947 --> 00:06:42,490
I already received treatment?

52
00:06:44,033 --> 00:06:44,951
No.

53
00:06:46,244 --> 00:06:48,079
You weren't ready.

54
00:06:54,419 --> 00:06:55,586
I'm dumbfounded.

55
00:06:57,713 --> 00:06:59,173
How could I forget that?

56
00:07:02,051 --> 00:07:04,762
What if I lose all my memory?

57
00:07:05,388 --> 00:07:07,932
I'm already sick as is.
That'd be so unfair.

58
00:07:11,602 --> 00:07:12,478
There are times

59
00:07:14,564 --> 00:07:17,066
when people completely forget things

60
00:07:18,276 --> 00:07:19,569
even if they're not sick.

61
00:07:24,115 --> 00:07:25,616
I was the same.

62
00:07:28,828 --> 00:07:29,871
I had forgotten it all.

63
00:07:31,664 --> 00:07:32,498
What is it?

64
00:07:33,499 --> 00:07:34,584
What's going on?

65
00:07:34,667 --> 00:07:37,170
Is there something else I forgot?

66
00:07:41,883 --> 00:07:44,552
I was going to divorce you

67
00:07:46,220 --> 00:07:47,847
without telling you first.

68
00:07:51,058 --> 00:07:51,976
What?

69
00:07:53,311 --> 00:07:55,229
And you found out in Germany.

70
00:07:56,898 --> 00:07:58,941
So it's been rocky for us lately.

71
00:08:00,818 --> 00:08:02,028
So…

72
00:08:02,987 --> 00:08:04,572
you were going

73
00:08:05,573 --> 00:08:07,241
to divorce me?

74
00:08:08,201 --> 00:08:09,035
Yes.

75
00:08:13,122 --> 00:08:15,166
And I knew?

76
00:08:16,334 --> 00:08:17,251
Yes.

77
00:08:19,086 --> 00:08:19,962
Don't lie.

78
00:08:21,130 --> 00:08:22,089
If that were true,

79
00:08:23,090 --> 00:08:25,176
then you wouldn't be here right now.

80
00:08:25,676 --> 00:08:28,179
I would've broken your bones
or popped your eardrums.

81
00:08:28,930 --> 00:08:30,932
-Hae-in--
-Should I do that right now?

82
00:08:31,015 --> 00:08:33,267
I have no idea what's going on.

83
00:08:33,351 --> 00:08:35,019
Then try to remember

84
00:08:36,354 --> 00:08:38,523
what I did to you…

85
00:08:41,150 --> 00:08:44,111
and how much you resented me.

86
00:08:44,195 --> 00:08:48,074
No, I really don't remember…

87
00:08:49,367 --> 00:08:50,868
So you won't bother trying anymore?

88
00:08:50,952 --> 00:08:53,204
I'd be grateful if you divorced me
without filing a suit.

89
00:08:53,287 --> 00:08:55,122
It was unbearable to live with you anyway.

90
00:08:55,206 --> 00:08:56,207
Hae-in.

91
00:08:57,708 --> 00:09:00,336
You know what kind of person you are.

92
00:09:00,419 --> 00:09:01,963
No wonder I chose to do so.

93
00:09:02,046 --> 00:09:03,714
I could've lived

94
00:09:03,798 --> 00:09:05,049
a comfortable and wealthy life.

95
00:09:05,132 --> 00:09:06,759
Because I hated living with you

96
00:09:06,842 --> 00:09:08,094
more than anything!

97
00:09:08,177 --> 00:09:10,471
When I heard that you'd be dying soon,

98
00:09:10,555 --> 00:09:11,639
I was relieved deep down.

99
00:09:11,722 --> 00:09:14,642
We'd have a clean divorce if I put up
with you for the next three months.

100
00:09:14,725 --> 00:09:16,519
So if you choose

101
00:09:16,602 --> 00:09:19,188
not to take any action at all
and just divorce me,

102
00:09:19,272 --> 00:09:20,481
then honestly,

103
00:09:20,565 --> 00:09:21,691
I'd be grateful.

104
00:09:22,650 --> 00:09:23,859
Will you do that?

105
00:09:36,205 --> 00:09:38,165
-Hae-in-.
-Stop. I remember now.

106
00:09:40,626 --> 00:09:43,462
I remember how much you despise me

107
00:09:44,922 --> 00:09:47,133
and how miserable your life has become.

108
00:09:48,092 --> 00:09:49,135
What is it?

109
00:09:50,303 --> 00:09:52,346
Did you think you'd live comfortably

110
00:09:52,430 --> 00:09:55,016
if you married me,
but found out that wasn't the case?

111
00:09:56,851 --> 00:09:58,644
It must've been entertaining

112
00:09:59,395 --> 00:10:02,189
to watch me not remember anything
and talk nonsense.

113
00:10:03,149 --> 00:10:04,150
No.

114
00:10:04,817 --> 00:10:06,861
-I wasn't--
-I was miserable too!

115
00:10:08,863 --> 00:10:09,864
It wasn't just you.

116
00:10:10,906 --> 00:10:11,949
I was miserable too.

117
00:10:15,536 --> 00:10:17,204
I can't spend my remaining life

118
00:10:17,913 --> 00:10:18,998
next to you.

119
00:10:19,624 --> 00:10:22,168
-Hae-in, wait.
-Let's part ways.

120
00:10:26,922 --> 00:10:28,007
I want a divorce.

121
00:10:48,152 --> 00:10:49,570
EPISODE 8

122
00:10:52,114 --> 00:10:53,658
ALARM

123
00:11:13,969 --> 00:11:16,263
It's a consensual divorce.

124
00:11:16,347 --> 00:11:18,974
So why are we here when you agreed
to divorce without any alimony?

125
00:11:19,725 --> 00:11:21,560
Who's their attorney?

126
00:11:21,644 --> 00:11:22,478
I'm not sure.

127
00:11:23,187 --> 00:11:26,232
This doesn't sit right with me.

128
00:12:01,267 --> 00:12:03,853
It must be him.
He must be her divorce attorney.

129
00:12:06,105 --> 00:12:08,983
-So?
-You don't know anything, do you?

130
00:12:09,066 --> 00:12:10,192
He's…

131
00:12:10,901 --> 00:12:11,819
a terrifying man.

132
00:12:11,902 --> 00:12:14,155
He's just an attorney.

133
00:12:15,740 --> 00:12:18,200
There are many rumors about who he is.

134
00:12:18,784 --> 00:12:20,494
The youngest heir
of a conglomerate family.

135
00:12:20,578 --> 00:12:22,538
A former soldier stationed abroad.

136
00:12:22,621 --> 00:12:24,707
Someone who came here on a spaceship.

137
00:12:24,790 --> 00:12:27,668
Others say he's a werewolf.

138
00:12:27,752 --> 00:12:29,670
His name is Vincenzo.

139
00:12:30,296 --> 00:12:31,505
And he is…

140
00:12:32,590 --> 00:12:33,841
Please show mercy.

141
00:12:33,924 --> 00:12:35,301
Please spare us.

142
00:12:35,384 --> 00:12:36,302
-Please.
-Please.

143
00:12:36,385 --> 00:12:38,262
-Just this once.
-Please spare us.

144
00:12:40,598 --> 00:12:41,599
He's from the mafia.

145
00:12:41,682 --> 00:12:42,641
The mafia?

146
00:12:43,309 --> 00:12:45,728
You mean the mafia from that Mafia game?

147
00:12:45,811 --> 00:12:48,939
No, the real mafia.
And he's a consigliere.

148
00:12:49,023 --> 00:12:50,441
He's the boss.

149
00:12:51,192 --> 00:12:53,027
I thought he was in Italy.

150
00:12:53,652 --> 00:12:55,279
I heard

151
00:12:55,946 --> 00:12:57,865
he doesn't negotiate in words.

152
00:12:59,074 --> 00:13:01,076
You don't deserve to be reasoned with.

153
00:13:23,432 --> 00:13:26,769
I think Ms. Hong has decided
not to forgive you.

154
00:13:26,852 --> 00:13:30,481
In all honesty,
what you did to her is infuriating.

155
00:13:30,564 --> 00:13:32,817
You tricked her into thinking
that you were in love.

156
00:13:33,901 --> 00:13:35,319
You told me…

157
00:13:35,903 --> 00:13:36,904
So?

158
00:13:38,155 --> 00:13:39,949
She probably wants you dead.

159
00:13:40,741 --> 00:13:43,577
Hae-in, please spare me this once!

160
00:13:45,079 --> 00:13:47,248
Mr. Baek, you deceived my client.

161
00:13:47,331 --> 00:13:49,792
A couple of divorce papers
won't make up for that.

162
00:13:52,545 --> 00:13:55,840
I'm sorry to say this,
but evil should be countered with evil.

163
00:13:57,216 --> 00:13:59,426
No!

164
00:14:01,470 --> 00:14:02,847
Hae-in, it was Yang-gi.

165
00:14:02,930 --> 00:14:04,974
He told me to do this.

166
00:14:05,558 --> 00:14:06,475
That bastard--

167
00:14:08,060 --> 00:14:09,270
That's her plan.

168
00:14:10,145 --> 00:14:11,105
Be quiet.

169
00:14:12,356 --> 00:14:13,899
Can I just leave?

170
00:14:13,983 --> 00:14:15,693
I have a family.

171
00:14:15,776 --> 00:14:18,863
You have no kids
and won't have a wife soon either.

172
00:14:20,614 --> 00:14:21,866
Do as you wish.

173
00:14:23,242 --> 00:14:24,618
Jeez.

174
00:14:34,169 --> 00:14:35,588
First of all, please know

175
00:14:36,338 --> 00:14:38,382
that I'm not here to negotiate.

176
00:14:51,770 --> 00:14:54,315
That's the official paper
regarding the divorce

177
00:14:54,398 --> 00:14:56,317
that Mr. Baek prepared. Correct?

178
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,401
Yes.

179
00:14:58,027 --> 00:14:59,570
-What's wrong with it?
-Look at it.

180
00:14:59,653 --> 00:15:01,196
He wrote the main reason for divorce

181
00:15:02,531 --> 00:15:04,575
as irreconcilable differences.

182
00:15:06,911 --> 00:15:08,078
These darn…

183
00:15:09,538 --> 00:15:10,581
nutjobs.

184
00:15:13,292 --> 00:15:16,587
Isn't that the simplest
and most optimal reason?

185
00:15:20,799 --> 00:15:22,009
Look at her.

186
00:15:22,092 --> 00:15:25,262
She's a wealthy woman
who's known for her good looks.

187
00:15:25,346 --> 00:15:27,806
This department store CEO
was born into a rich family.

188
00:15:27,890 --> 00:15:30,434
The tabloids and rumors make her out
to be someone haughty.

189
00:15:30,517 --> 00:15:32,895
And she's a member
of the One Trillion Club.

190
00:15:35,689 --> 00:15:36,690
Not yet.

191
00:15:40,152 --> 00:15:42,655
Well, not yet.

192
00:15:42,738 --> 00:15:44,448
Anyway, given these facts,

193
00:15:44,531 --> 00:15:47,618
not many would think
that her personality is her forte.

194
00:15:47,701 --> 00:15:49,036
And now,

195
00:15:50,913 --> 00:15:53,791
she's going to divorce a mere director

196
00:15:53,874 --> 00:15:55,626
due to irreconcilable differences?

197
00:15:58,379 --> 00:16:02,466
People will immediately think
that she has a terrible personality, no?

198
00:16:03,342 --> 00:16:04,510
Right.

199
00:16:05,344 --> 00:16:08,764
Then what should we say instead?
Do you have any suggestions?

200
00:16:09,932 --> 00:16:10,933
I do.

201
00:16:14,436 --> 00:16:17,106
"They have become distant
due to their hectic schedules."

202
00:16:17,189 --> 00:16:18,816
But they live under the same roof.

203
00:16:21,986 --> 00:16:24,613
"They have agreed
to remain as good friends."

204
00:16:24,697 --> 00:16:25,990
I don't think they can.

205
00:16:26,073 --> 00:16:28,742
-"They wish the best for each other."
-Wait.

206
00:16:29,702 --> 00:16:30,995
I don't wish that.

207
00:16:34,665 --> 00:16:38,002
From what I know,
none of my clients ever do.

208
00:16:38,085 --> 00:16:39,336
They just say this.

209
00:16:44,091 --> 00:16:46,760
You can write whatever you want.

210
00:16:49,221 --> 00:16:50,055
Are you sure?

211
00:16:51,473 --> 00:16:52,933
Will you not regret it?

212
00:16:54,268 --> 00:16:55,102
No.

213
00:16:56,020 --> 00:16:57,479
Whatever it may be,

214
00:16:58,355 --> 00:17:00,190
it won't be the real reason anyway.

215
00:17:34,058 --> 00:17:37,936
Why did you choose
the subway instead of a taxi or a car?

216
00:17:39,813 --> 00:17:40,773
You know.

217
00:17:41,482 --> 00:17:45,110
When I've had a rough day,
but have no one to rant to,

218
00:17:45,194 --> 00:17:46,153
I take Line Two.

219
00:17:46,945 --> 00:17:47,780
Why?

220
00:17:47,863 --> 00:17:49,656
This line is a loop,

221
00:17:50,324 --> 00:17:51,909
so it goes around Seoul.

222
00:17:51,992 --> 00:17:55,245
Time passes by quickly
when I watch people.

223
00:17:56,205 --> 00:17:58,373
I remain in the subway until sundown.

224
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:01,710
Then in between
Dangsan and Hapjeong Stations,

225
00:18:04,963 --> 00:18:07,382
I get to see the best sunset in Seoul.

226
00:18:26,985 --> 00:18:28,237
Isn't it pretty?

227
00:18:28,320 --> 00:18:31,323
The sunset helps me forget

228
00:18:31,406 --> 00:18:34,118
how awful of a day I had.

229
00:18:34,201 --> 00:18:37,079
It just makes me want to go home.

230
00:19:13,615 --> 00:19:14,616
Sir.

231
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:17,202
Let's make a stop somewhere.

232
00:19:30,174 --> 00:19:34,136
He had rice soup, played baseball,
washed his car,

233
00:19:35,554 --> 00:19:36,430
ran laps,

234
00:19:37,598 --> 00:19:39,099
and had rice soup again.

235
00:19:39,808 --> 00:19:41,101
Is it that good?

236
00:19:42,227 --> 00:19:44,813
He had stir-fried pork too.
He eats so well.

237
00:19:44,897 --> 00:19:46,690
Look at you. You're running again.

238
00:19:50,277 --> 00:19:51,528
He runs so well.

239
00:19:52,154 --> 00:19:53,530
What's his deal? Gosh.

240
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:04,208
-Go slowly. You'll hurt yourself.
-Be careful.

241
00:20:04,833 --> 00:20:06,752
Me too.

242
00:20:08,503 --> 00:20:10,380
They're all working out in pairs,

243
00:20:11,256 --> 00:20:13,008
so why does he run alone?

244
00:20:19,973 --> 00:20:21,391
Is this fun?

245
00:20:23,060 --> 00:20:24,186
Is it really?

246
00:20:58,011 --> 00:20:59,471
GRANDMA'S HOME COOKING

247
00:20:59,554 --> 00:21:02,474
Two bowls of rice soup
and one soju, please.

248
00:21:02,557 --> 00:21:03,392
Coming up.

249
00:21:06,019 --> 00:21:07,271
It won't take long.

250
00:21:07,354 --> 00:21:08,605
Thank you.

251
00:21:10,190 --> 00:21:11,233
What do you want?

252
00:21:12,567 --> 00:21:14,444
One bowl of rice soup and one soju.

253
00:21:15,279 --> 00:21:16,154
What?

254
00:21:16,989 --> 00:21:19,700
One bowl of rice soup
and one soju, please.

255
00:21:20,325 --> 00:21:22,744
"One bowl of rice soup
and one soju." Okay.

256
00:21:34,589 --> 00:21:36,466
You couldn't have sundae and rice soup

257
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:39,469
because your wife hated the smell,
but you can knock yourself out now.

258
00:21:39,553 --> 00:21:41,346
This is a perk of the divorce.

259
00:21:41,430 --> 00:21:44,057
Just think of the good things.

260
00:21:44,141 --> 00:21:46,768
Look. You no longer
have to worry about men tailing you

261
00:21:46,852 --> 00:21:48,353
or having to rush home.

262
00:21:48,437 --> 00:21:49,688
You had to leave us

263
00:21:49,771 --> 00:21:52,858
while drinking if your mother-in-law
or the chairman called you.

264
00:21:52,941 --> 00:21:56,737
Jeez. That's why you didn't meet us often,
and always had dinner alone.

265
00:22:00,657 --> 00:22:02,159
I know,

266
00:22:02,242 --> 00:22:03,952
but I wanted that life.

267
00:22:04,036 --> 00:22:07,998
What do you mean? You wanted that?
Do you have Stockholm syndrome?

268
00:22:08,081 --> 00:22:09,624
I don't know.

269
00:22:09,708 --> 00:22:10,876
I just wanted

270
00:22:12,127 --> 00:22:14,171
to be by Hae-in's side.

271
00:22:33,315 --> 00:22:34,775
About those pills, sir,

272
00:22:34,858 --> 00:22:36,318
I'll send you an email too,

273
00:22:36,401 --> 00:22:39,529
but they're used
to treat malignant tumors.

274
00:22:39,613 --> 00:22:41,698
It's an anticancer drug.

275
00:22:41,782 --> 00:22:43,742
-Are you sure?
-Yes, I'm sure.

276
00:22:58,465 --> 00:22:59,883
Mom!

277
00:23:05,222 --> 00:23:06,807
EVERGREEN HOPE ORPHANAGE

278
00:23:06,890 --> 00:23:07,724
Mom!

279
00:23:24,366 --> 00:23:25,742
Hey! You!

280
00:23:26,410 --> 00:23:27,828
You! It's okay.

281
00:23:27,911 --> 00:23:29,371
It's okay. Hey.

282
00:23:30,205 --> 00:23:31,706
You scumbag!

283
00:23:31,790 --> 00:23:33,583
What if my dog got hurt?

284
00:23:33,667 --> 00:23:35,335
Have you gone insane?

285
00:23:35,419 --> 00:23:37,879
Do you know how expensive this dog is?

286
00:23:38,713 --> 00:23:40,424
-What are you looking at?
-Stop it.

287
00:23:41,049 --> 00:23:43,218
I almost got bitten by your dog.

288
00:23:43,301 --> 00:23:44,594
And who are you?

289
00:23:45,262 --> 00:23:47,639
Do they not teach you manners?

290
00:23:47,722 --> 00:23:49,099
Ms. Hong!

291
00:23:54,938 --> 00:23:55,939
Hae-in.

292
00:23:56,857 --> 00:23:58,191
Grandpa.

293
00:23:58,275 --> 00:24:00,193
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

294
00:24:00,277 --> 00:24:01,236
Are you?

295
00:24:01,945 --> 00:24:04,489
She's the granddaughter
of Queens Group's chairman.

296
00:24:04,573 --> 00:24:05,657
Goodness, I didn't know.

297
00:24:06,116 --> 00:24:07,826
Are you okay?

298
00:24:07,909 --> 00:24:09,327
Let's go to the hospital.

299
00:24:09,411 --> 00:24:10,537
Okay?

300
00:24:10,620 --> 00:24:11,872
Goodness.

301
00:24:42,777 --> 00:24:43,778
Thanks.

302
00:25:33,578 --> 00:25:36,373
Mr. Oh, where's Hae-in?
She hasn't come home yet.

303
00:25:36,456 --> 00:25:38,583
She told me to go home first.

304
00:25:38,667 --> 00:25:40,669
She got off at a nearby elementary school.

305
00:25:40,752 --> 00:25:42,337
You should've kept an eye on her.

306
00:25:42,420 --> 00:25:45,006
I haven't been able to track her
since she's been alone lately.

307
00:25:45,757 --> 00:25:47,592
This isn't what we agreed on.

308
00:25:47,676 --> 00:25:48,927
I'm sorry, sir.

309
00:26:00,230 --> 00:26:02,357
Where have you been?
Why did you take a taxi?

310
00:26:03,024 --> 00:26:04,609
I had to stop by somewhere.

311
00:26:05,110 --> 00:26:05,944
Wait.

312
00:26:07,529 --> 00:26:10,407
Will Mr. Baek keep working for you?
Aren't you uncomfortable?

313
00:26:12,033 --> 00:26:14,953
I don't plan on firing him
if he wants to stay.

314
00:26:15,036 --> 00:26:17,497
After all, we need him in the company.

315
00:26:18,873 --> 00:26:20,333
The one person Queens really needs

316
00:26:22,919 --> 00:26:23,753
is me.

317
00:26:25,797 --> 00:26:26,715
And I'm also

318
00:26:27,674 --> 00:26:28,675
the one you need.

319
00:26:30,010 --> 00:26:31,928
Must I still prove that?

320
00:26:36,141 --> 00:26:38,810
I was going to tell you later,

321
00:26:39,644 --> 00:26:41,146
but I'll just say it now.

322
00:26:41,229 --> 00:26:42,897
I thought long and hard.

323
00:26:43,732 --> 00:26:44,983
I'm going to pass up

324
00:26:46,026 --> 00:26:47,068
on Hercyna.

325
00:26:47,569 --> 00:26:48,737
What?

326
00:26:50,030 --> 00:26:52,782
I appreciate all the help you've given me.

327
00:26:52,866 --> 00:26:55,076
But Mr. Hermann chose our store

328
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:58,371
because of you, not me.

329
00:26:58,455 --> 00:27:01,625
I wanted to use you out of greed,

330
00:27:01,708 --> 00:27:03,501
-but that's--
-Then do so.

331
00:27:04,127 --> 00:27:05,545
That's why I'm here.

332
00:27:05,629 --> 00:27:08,757
Do you know what I've done in life
to become someone useful to you?

333
00:27:10,967 --> 00:27:11,926
Do I have to know?

334
00:27:16,931 --> 00:27:17,766
Hae-in.

335
00:27:17,849 --> 00:27:21,227
I'm not going to ask you
for anything even if you choose Hercyna.

336
00:27:21,936 --> 00:27:24,522
All I wanted to do was show you

337
00:27:25,982 --> 00:27:28,443
that I could provide you with everything

338
00:27:29,861 --> 00:27:30,695
others couldn't.

339
00:27:34,240 --> 00:27:37,786
You're being blunt since I'm divorced now.

340
00:27:38,787 --> 00:27:39,829
But listen up.

341
00:27:40,914 --> 00:27:43,500
I didn't divorce him
so you could have a chance.

342
00:27:43,583 --> 00:27:47,003
I married Hyun-woo
because he said he'd be by my side.

343
00:27:48,046 --> 00:27:51,424
And I divorced him
because I felt bad about everything

344
00:27:52,801 --> 00:27:53,760
he had to go through.

345
00:27:56,721 --> 00:27:58,431
Can you say the same thing

346
00:27:59,516 --> 00:28:01,476
even if you lost everything?

347
00:28:01,559 --> 00:28:03,228
-What?
-Even then?

348
00:28:05,063 --> 00:28:05,897
You won't need me?

349
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:09,859
Did you just get home?

350
00:28:41,766 --> 00:28:44,769
You went through so much, ma'am.

351
00:28:44,853 --> 00:28:48,314
-He's always been a nuisance.
-And he still is.

352
00:28:48,398 --> 00:28:51,443
Why isn't Hyun-woo quitting his job?

353
00:28:51,526 --> 00:28:52,902
You should fire him.

354
00:28:54,028 --> 00:28:57,073
Mom, if there's one thing I can't do,
it's outsmarting him.

355
00:28:57,991 --> 00:28:59,492
What do you mean?

356
00:29:00,410 --> 00:29:02,787
He divorced her without taking any money.

357
00:29:02,871 --> 00:29:04,456
What if we provoke him,

358
00:29:04,539 --> 00:29:07,584
and he uses that smart brain
of his to get alimony?

359
00:29:07,667 --> 00:29:11,796
But still,
a legal director has a lot of power.

360
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:14,466
Don't you feel uneasy
that he still has that power?

361
00:29:14,549 --> 00:29:16,468
I do.

362
00:29:16,551 --> 00:29:18,970
That's why you should get rid of him.

363
00:29:21,389 --> 00:29:23,475
Goodness, why is she calling me?

364
00:29:25,602 --> 00:29:27,312
You have no customers. Good.

365
00:29:28,062 --> 00:29:30,064
Mom, why are you here?

366
00:29:30,148 --> 00:29:33,485
I want to look like a female politician.

367
00:29:33,568 --> 00:29:35,487
-Turn me into one.
-What?

368
00:29:35,570 --> 00:29:38,239
You know that hairstyle they have

369
00:29:38,323 --> 00:29:40,909
when giving a public apology to show that

370
00:29:40,992 --> 00:29:42,744
they're terribly sorry?

371
00:29:42,827 --> 00:29:47,165
But I don't want to look servile.

372
00:29:47,248 --> 00:29:49,501
-There's no such hairstyle.
-Come on!

373
00:29:49,584 --> 00:29:53,046
Give my hair some poof like this.

374
00:29:53,129 --> 00:29:55,173
I see. Poof.

375
00:29:55,256 --> 00:29:58,384
Yes, I need some poof to look confident.

376
00:30:03,723 --> 00:30:05,600
I felt awful

377
00:30:06,142 --> 00:30:08,144
after our previous call.

378
00:30:08,228 --> 00:30:11,064
Marriage is the most important promise
in one's life.

379
00:30:11,147 --> 00:30:14,108
Hae-in must be so distraught.

380
00:30:14,192 --> 00:30:18,613
I'm sure you and your husband
were utterly speechless as well.

381
00:30:19,489 --> 00:30:21,991
I should've taught my son better.

382
00:30:22,075 --> 00:30:23,785
I'm truly sorry.

383
00:30:26,704 --> 00:30:28,665
-Is this a scheme?
-Sorry?

384
00:30:28,748 --> 00:30:32,043
Did your attorney son tell you to do this
so that he could get alimony

385
00:30:32,126 --> 00:30:33,837
and some of Hae-in's fortune?

386
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:34,963
Sorry?

387
00:30:35,296 --> 00:30:37,590
Don't tell me you're recording this.

388
00:30:37,674 --> 00:30:41,010
You can't use this recording in court
since I didn't consent to it.

389
00:30:41,094 --> 00:30:43,888
Recording? Why would I do such a thing?

390
00:30:43,972 --> 00:30:46,474
Why wouldn't you? Even your son did it.

391
00:30:46,558 --> 00:30:48,560
-Hyun-woo?
-Yes.

392
00:30:48,643 --> 00:30:51,980
He bugged our chairman's room.

393
00:30:52,063 --> 00:30:54,858
I don't know if he wanted
to sell the recording

394
00:30:54,941 --> 00:30:57,986
or use it against Hae-in
for their divorce.

395
00:30:58,653 --> 00:31:01,698
What did he say? Did he admit to it?

396
00:31:01,781 --> 00:31:04,534
-He denied it.
-Then that's the truth.

397
00:31:04,617 --> 00:31:07,287
Does it even matter anymore?

398
00:31:07,370 --> 00:31:08,538
They're divorced now.

399
00:31:11,583 --> 00:31:13,126
I guess you didn't know.

400
00:31:14,210 --> 00:31:18,631
This is exactly why some people
shouldn't marry each other.

401
00:31:18,715 --> 00:31:20,633
They'll only bring each other down.

402
00:31:20,717 --> 00:31:23,511
That's why I was vehemently against them.

403
00:31:27,891 --> 00:31:29,893
You may have been against them,

404
00:31:29,976 --> 00:31:34,272
but they shared
enough happy memories to get married.

405
00:31:35,189 --> 00:31:36,190
What?

406
00:31:36,274 --> 00:31:38,902
I realized that life may seem long,

407
00:31:38,985 --> 00:31:41,696
but happy memories are limited.

408
00:31:43,156 --> 00:31:44,032
So?

409
00:31:44,115 --> 00:31:46,034
They may have parted ways,

410
00:31:46,117 --> 00:31:48,036
but I hope

411
00:31:48,119 --> 00:31:50,371
they'll still cherish

412
00:31:50,455 --> 00:31:54,125
those happy memories.

413
00:31:54,208 --> 00:31:56,044
That's a good idea.

414
00:31:56,127 --> 00:31:58,630
The divorce has already been settled,

415
00:31:58,713 --> 00:32:04,260
so I hope your family
won't try to get anything out of it.

416
00:32:04,344 --> 00:32:08,222
Also, please persuade him to quit his job.

417
00:32:08,306 --> 00:32:11,267
Why won't he? He's so pathetic.

418
00:32:12,435 --> 00:32:15,271
I hope we never see each other again.

419
00:32:27,533 --> 00:32:29,494
Goodness.

420
00:32:30,078 --> 00:32:32,246
Did she not say who she was meeting?

421
00:32:32,330 --> 00:32:34,499
Judging by how she dressed
before going to Seoul,

422
00:32:35,124 --> 00:32:36,167
maybe it was Ms. Kim.

423
00:32:36,250 --> 00:32:38,252
Then why isn't she picking up?

424
00:32:40,129 --> 00:32:41,714
There she is! Mom!

425
00:32:44,884 --> 00:32:48,471
I gave her hair so much poof,
but it's all gone.

426
00:32:48,554 --> 00:32:50,098
Go greet her.

427
00:32:50,181 --> 00:32:51,015
Grandma!

428
00:32:51,099 --> 00:32:54,519
Hello, my dear puppy.

429
00:32:54,602 --> 00:32:56,229
-Were you waiting for me?
-Yes.

430
00:32:57,730 --> 00:33:00,108
-My feet hurt, so I bought some slippers.
-Well done.

431
00:33:02,068 --> 00:33:04,320
I was worried
since you weren't picking up.

432
00:33:06,781 --> 00:33:07,824
Did you have dinner?

433
00:33:11,703 --> 00:33:12,787
Not yet.

434
00:33:16,082 --> 00:33:18,001
Hey, order some Chinese.

435
00:33:18,084 --> 00:33:21,045
Forget it. We should have rice.

436
00:33:22,839 --> 00:33:24,424
Where should I order from? Ting Hua?

437
00:33:24,507 --> 00:33:25,842
No, they're not good.

438
00:33:25,925 --> 00:33:28,428
The Great Wall of China
has better service.

439
00:33:29,220 --> 00:33:30,388
Do you have coupons?

440
00:33:33,599 --> 00:33:35,852
That's the list of customers who purchased

441
00:33:35,935 --> 00:33:38,271
Ronde de Frédic's 101st anniversary watch.

442
00:33:38,354 --> 00:33:40,732
There's one Korean.

443
00:33:40,815 --> 00:33:42,942
Isn't she the chairman's mistress?

444
00:33:43,901 --> 00:33:44,861
Where was it purchased?

445
00:33:44,944 --> 00:33:47,030
Six years ago on Fifth Avenue, Manhattan.

446
00:33:48,740 --> 00:33:49,949
It's a men's watch.

447
00:33:50,658 --> 00:33:52,285
I wonder whom she gifted it to.

448
00:33:56,247 --> 00:34:00,376
She goes somewhere without me
about two to three times a week.

449
00:34:39,582 --> 00:34:40,666
Our cars

450
00:34:41,626 --> 00:34:43,461
are fine. We didn't crash.

451
00:34:43,544 --> 00:34:45,421
-Is this a coincidence?
-No.

452
00:34:46,130 --> 00:34:48,341
I saw you following Hae-in
from the office,

453
00:34:48,424 --> 00:34:49,759
so I followed you.

454
00:34:49,842 --> 00:34:52,553
They're used to treat malignant tumors.

455
00:34:52,637 --> 00:34:54,180
It's an anticancer drug.

456
00:34:55,056 --> 00:34:55,932
Yes, I'm sure.

457
00:34:56,015 --> 00:34:57,558
Is someone you know sick?

458
00:34:58,351 --> 00:34:59,352
Hello?

459
00:35:00,311 --> 00:35:01,312
Mr. Yoon?

460
00:35:16,494 --> 00:35:17,370
CALLS

461
00:35:17,453 --> 00:35:18,913
YOON EUN-SUNG

462
00:35:21,040 --> 00:35:23,126
I reported back to him every now and then

463
00:35:23,209 --> 00:35:25,711
about whom you were meeting.

464
00:35:25,795 --> 00:35:28,506
He told me to look into these pills,
so I asked a friend

465
00:35:28,589 --> 00:35:30,842
who worked at a pharmaceutical company.

466
00:35:30,925 --> 00:35:31,759
I'm truly sorry.

467
00:35:32,677 --> 00:35:34,345
Why are you following her?

468
00:35:34,428 --> 00:35:35,888
She's not your wife anymore.

469
00:35:37,515 --> 00:35:39,433
So what's it to you?

470
00:35:41,561 --> 00:35:46,607
Look. If you continue to follow her,
I won't stop following you either.

471
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:51,154
And if you try to harm her,
I'll do the same to you.

472
00:35:52,155 --> 00:35:53,281
That's my plan.

473
00:35:53,364 --> 00:35:55,449
So you want to protect her.

474
00:35:56,200 --> 00:35:57,285
Do as you please.

475
00:35:57,368 --> 00:35:59,704
She'll choose me anyway.

476
00:36:01,164 --> 00:36:02,957
You'll get what I mean soon.

477
00:36:24,604 --> 00:36:27,690
Did your family immigrate there
or were you studying abroad?

478
00:36:27,773 --> 00:36:29,192
I was adopted overseas.

479
00:36:30,109 --> 00:36:33,070
My adoptive parents passed away
right before I graduated university.

480
00:36:33,654 --> 00:36:36,073
So I have no family now.

481
00:36:40,786 --> 00:36:41,704
Come in.

482
00:36:45,416 --> 00:36:46,918
Eun-sung.

483
00:36:47,585 --> 00:36:49,754
I could've just gone to you.

484
00:36:50,463 --> 00:36:51,839
It was urgent.

485
00:36:53,382 --> 00:36:55,218
Mr. Na of Bolt One called.

486
00:36:55,301 --> 00:36:56,135
What? What for?

487
00:36:56,219 --> 00:36:57,720
Regarding the land.

488
00:36:57,803 --> 00:37:00,765
There's a military base near the area
where the resort will be built.

489
00:37:00,848 --> 00:37:02,808
Gosh, is that what this is about?

490
00:37:02,892 --> 00:37:04,852
They agreed to move.

491
00:37:04,936 --> 00:37:08,189
If not, their laser station would've made
the construction impossible.

492
00:37:08,272 --> 00:37:10,024
I heard they're not moving.

493
00:37:11,275 --> 00:37:12,109
What?

494
00:37:17,740 --> 00:37:20,618
Why did they change their mind?

495
00:37:20,701 --> 00:37:23,996
MOLIT wants to move, but the MND refused
and said it'd cost too much.

496
00:37:24,080 --> 00:37:26,165
So they canceled everything.

497
00:37:26,749 --> 00:37:29,377
Is the MND more powerful than the MOLIT?

498
00:37:31,754 --> 00:37:32,922
I'm not too sure, sir.

499
00:37:33,464 --> 00:37:35,800
The MOLIT must win at all costs.

500
00:37:35,883 --> 00:37:38,135
Can you still not reach
the senior manager of MOLIT?

501
00:37:38,219 --> 00:37:40,179
No, he keeps texting
that he's in a meeting.

502
00:37:40,263 --> 00:37:42,807
He can't do this to me.

503
00:38:00,491 --> 00:38:01,826
GRANDFATHER

504
00:38:22,555 --> 00:38:23,639
Hello?

505
00:38:23,723 --> 00:38:24,974
Yes, sir.

506
00:38:26,642 --> 00:38:27,685
-Sir.
-What is it?

507
00:38:27,768 --> 00:38:30,104
-The chairman wants to see you.
-No…

508
00:38:30,730 --> 00:38:32,898
Why can't you be quick-witted?

509
00:38:32,982 --> 00:38:36,652
Didn't you see how I rejected
his call for the first time in my life?

510
00:38:36,736 --> 00:38:37,611
Yes, I did.

511
00:38:37,695 --> 00:38:39,822
You should have made up an excuse.

512
00:38:39,905 --> 00:38:42,700
How could you just say yes?

513
00:38:44,160 --> 00:38:46,245
Hyun-woo. Where is he?

514
00:38:46,329 --> 00:38:47,538
Hyun-woo.

515
00:38:49,415 --> 00:38:52,626
Hyun-woo,
it must've been so tough for you.

516
00:38:52,710 --> 00:38:54,837
-What's wrong?
-You know what they say.

517
00:38:54,920 --> 00:38:57,506
Workers have resignation letters
ready at all times.

518
00:38:57,590 --> 00:39:00,384
So why can't you have
divorce papers in your safe?

519
00:39:00,468 --> 00:39:01,927
It's not your fault.

520
00:39:02,011 --> 00:39:03,721
It's our family's for discovering it.

521
00:39:05,014 --> 00:39:06,265
What's this about?

522
00:39:06,349 --> 00:39:08,351
-An issue with the site.
-What?

523
00:39:08,434 --> 00:39:11,687
The military base needs to move
so that people can visit our resort,

524
00:39:11,771 --> 00:39:14,065
take the elevator to the sky lounge,

525
00:39:14,148 --> 00:39:15,608
have some steak and wine,

526
00:39:15,691 --> 00:39:19,612
stargaze, and swim in the infinity pool.

527
00:39:20,529 --> 00:39:23,157
-But they won't move.
-I told you to run the validity test.

528
00:39:23,240 --> 00:39:24,241
I know.

529
00:39:24,325 --> 00:39:27,411
You did say that,
but Mr. Yoon swooped in at that moment

530
00:39:27,495 --> 00:39:29,455
and made such a tempting offer.

531
00:39:29,538 --> 00:39:31,040
So I was too hasty.

532
00:39:32,124 --> 00:39:33,584
I see. Then you should go to him.

533
00:39:33,667 --> 00:39:34,960
-Ask him for help.
-Come on!

534
00:39:35,461 --> 00:39:38,589
He's from the U.S.
He never served in the military.

535
00:39:38,672 --> 00:39:40,716
So what would he know about moving bases?

536
00:39:40,800 --> 00:39:43,177
On the other hand, you were a marine.

537
00:39:47,598 --> 00:39:50,476
Not just the marines,
but the Special Guard Team.

538
00:39:50,559 --> 00:39:51,477
See?

539
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:54,438
I'm only asking you for help
since you're special.

540
00:39:54,522 --> 00:39:55,940
Please save me.

541
00:39:57,691 --> 00:39:58,692
Honey.

542
00:40:00,694 --> 00:40:01,737
Yes?

543
00:40:02,905 --> 00:40:04,198
What were you doing?

544
00:40:04,281 --> 00:40:06,367
I'm in huge trouble.

545
00:40:06,450 --> 00:40:09,620
I'm missing the last piece
of this 2000-piece puzzle.

546
00:40:09,703 --> 00:40:11,247
Are you serious?

547
00:40:11,330 --> 00:40:13,833
Queens Group,
who ambitiously announced the building

548
00:40:13,916 --> 00:40:17,378
of the largest resort complex
in Northeast Asia, is facing bad luck.

549
00:40:17,461 --> 00:40:19,380
A military base nearby canceled

550
00:40:19,463 --> 00:40:21,924
their plans to move
and therefore, has limited

551
00:40:22,007 --> 00:40:24,135
the resort's height to 180 meters.

552
00:40:24,218 --> 00:40:28,806
This means that the hotel can only build
39 floors instead of the original 90.

553
00:40:28,889 --> 00:40:32,101
The hotel's estimated earnings
will likely drop drastically,

554
00:40:32,184 --> 00:40:34,812
and its investors may demand a prepayment…

555
00:40:35,563 --> 00:40:37,648
Is Soo-cheol still not answering?

556
00:40:38,399 --> 00:40:41,610
No, Father. I think he's trying
to resolve this issue--

557
00:40:41,694 --> 00:40:45,448
He shouldn't have let this happen
in the first place. It's too late!

558
00:40:45,531 --> 00:40:48,951
How is he just as foolish as you?

559
00:40:49,702 --> 00:40:50,661
Goodness.

560
00:40:52,872 --> 00:40:54,790
Hey, you were all here.

561
00:40:54,874 --> 00:40:56,584
Why haven't you been picking up?

562
00:40:56,667 --> 00:40:59,295
I'm here now with a solution.

563
00:41:03,424 --> 00:41:04,258
What is this?

564
00:41:07,636 --> 00:41:11,432
I looked into the long-range radar
near our land.

565
00:41:11,515 --> 00:41:15,811
Having been built in 1994,
it's worn out and needs to be repaired.

566
00:41:15,895 --> 00:41:17,730
Its efficiency rate is a bit over 60%,

567
00:41:17,813 --> 00:41:20,441
and it received Grade C
in last year's safety test.

568
00:41:20,524 --> 00:41:23,903
The government gave us money,
so it'll be fixed this summer.

569
00:41:23,986 --> 00:41:26,697
Raising the height of the radar.

570
00:41:26,780 --> 00:41:28,240
-What about that instead?
-Sorry?

571
00:41:33,871 --> 00:41:38,292
The radar station is 180 m,
and the hotel is 350 m.

572
00:41:38,375 --> 00:41:39,460
So if you set up

573
00:41:39,543 --> 00:41:43,923
a concrete structure
above the station that's 170 m or more,

574
00:41:45,007 --> 00:41:46,342
then the problem is solved.

575
00:41:46,425 --> 00:41:48,844
It seems like the optimal solution.

576
00:41:49,887 --> 00:41:50,804
Right.

577
00:41:51,514 --> 00:41:54,266
Hyun-woo sure is smart.

578
00:41:54,350 --> 00:41:57,853
I came up with the idea.
He just wrote it down as my attorney.

579
00:41:57,937 --> 00:42:00,231
Hyun-woo is quite intelligent.

580
00:42:03,859 --> 00:42:07,071
Why does it feel like
no one is listening to me?

581
00:42:07,154 --> 00:42:10,449
Anyway, make sure
you explain it well to the investors.

582
00:42:10,533 --> 00:42:14,119
You got it. I'm sure they'll be relieved.

583
00:42:14,954 --> 00:42:16,997
Did you not hear what I just said?

584
00:42:17,081 --> 00:42:20,668
The problem has been solved,
so why are you pulling out?

585
00:42:20,751 --> 00:42:22,419
I just don't get it.

586
00:42:22,503 --> 00:42:26,632
I heard Chairman Hong's financial manager
was taken in for interrogation.

587
00:42:26,715 --> 00:42:27,841
About that…

588
00:42:27,925 --> 00:42:30,511
How could you keep
such important news from us?

589
00:42:30,594 --> 00:42:34,056
I wouldn't have known
had it not been for our legal advisor.

590
00:42:35,349 --> 00:42:36,642
Your legal advisor?

591
00:42:38,060 --> 00:42:39,979
As in Apollon? Am I right?

592
00:42:41,063 --> 00:42:42,481
Mr. Baek planned it out well.

593
00:42:43,107 --> 00:42:45,067
No one would invest

594
00:42:45,150 --> 00:42:47,236
when the financial manager
has been arrested.

595
00:42:47,903 --> 00:42:49,363
I can't believe Hyun-woo.

596
00:42:50,322 --> 00:42:52,908
He should take revenge on Hae-in, not me.

597
00:42:54,076 --> 00:42:57,663
Is this the end
since they're all pulling out? Oh, God.

598
00:42:58,581 --> 00:42:59,415
Of course not.

599
00:43:00,291 --> 00:43:01,125
What?

600
00:43:01,208 --> 00:43:02,167
It's the beginning.

601
00:43:03,502 --> 00:43:05,337
Hey, does that mean…

602
00:43:08,716 --> 00:43:09,967
Sir.

603
00:43:10,050 --> 00:43:11,385
Take a look at this.

604
00:43:14,722 --> 00:43:17,766
P INVESTMENT PLANS TO INVEST
900 BILLION WON IN Q RESORT

605
00:43:23,105 --> 00:43:26,150
We, Pione Investment,
will be your sole investor.

606
00:43:26,233 --> 00:43:28,777
It'll be easier to sort things out
if we're the sole investor.

607
00:43:28,861 --> 00:43:30,779
Yes, a sole investor is the way to go.

608
00:43:30,863 --> 00:43:34,033
People say we shouldn't put
all our eggs in one basket,

609
00:43:34,116 --> 00:43:37,244
but it's completely fine
since we trust Eun-sung.

610
00:43:38,996 --> 00:43:41,040
Yes, it's all about who you work with.

611
00:43:41,123 --> 00:43:43,042
And I also value trust the most.

612
00:43:43,125 --> 00:43:46,086
Are you my soulmate or what?

613
00:43:46,170 --> 00:43:50,090
I always say that business
is about those involved.

614
00:43:51,467 --> 00:43:53,385
My entire life is in your hands.

615
00:43:54,053 --> 00:43:57,556
I'm sure this wasn't easy for you,
so thank you for doing this.

616
00:43:58,140 --> 00:44:00,726
I should seal the deal
before you change your mind.

617
00:44:10,527 --> 00:44:13,072
You shouldn't be here, sir.

618
00:44:15,407 --> 00:44:16,950
Hyun-woo, what is this about?

619
00:44:17,034 --> 00:44:18,118
Secretary Jang.

620
00:44:22,956 --> 00:44:26,627
Sir, the Legal Team gave their opinion
regarding this investment deal.

621
00:44:26,710 --> 00:44:30,047
But I don't think you received it.
Please reconsider the convertible rights.

622
00:44:31,131 --> 00:44:32,800
If the owner's risk causes a problem,

623
00:44:32,883 --> 00:44:36,637
then 6.7% of your shares
will be handed over to Mr. Yoon.

624
00:44:36,720 --> 00:44:38,722
You shouldn't be rash about this.

625
00:44:38,806 --> 00:44:39,765
Hyun-woo.

626
00:44:39,848 --> 00:44:40,974
Look, Mr. Baek!

627
00:44:41,058 --> 00:44:42,559
What he just said

628
00:44:43,435 --> 00:44:44,978
makes sense too.

629
00:44:46,230 --> 00:44:47,564
Father!

630
00:44:48,649 --> 00:44:49,858
You can do as you please.

631
00:44:49,942 --> 00:44:53,362
However, I will also pull out
if this falls through.

632
00:44:54,822 --> 00:44:55,906
The trust

633
00:44:56,657 --> 00:44:58,075
needs to be mutual.

634
00:45:10,379 --> 00:45:13,090
She said you'll have to make
a big decision soon.

635
00:45:13,757 --> 00:45:16,969
If someone offers you
a large sum of money and some papers,

636
00:45:17,052 --> 00:45:18,554
she advises that you accept it.

637
00:45:18,637 --> 00:45:22,141
Doing so will save you and your company.

638
00:45:23,851 --> 00:45:26,103
Whoever hurls a monkey wrench into it

639
00:45:26,729 --> 00:45:30,107
will betray you down the road,

640
00:45:30,190 --> 00:45:31,775
so you should ignore them.

641
00:45:32,985 --> 00:45:34,194
Come on.

642
00:45:37,740 --> 00:45:39,616
You must listen to me.

643
00:45:40,242 --> 00:45:44,455
Just like at that hunting ground,
this great shaman has saved your life

644
00:45:44,538 --> 00:45:46,206
countless times.

645
00:45:47,750 --> 00:45:49,460
She sure is good.

646
00:45:49,543 --> 00:45:50,836
Sorry?

647
00:45:51,754 --> 00:45:52,588
It's nothing.

648
00:45:53,630 --> 00:45:55,007
-Hyun-woo?
-Yes, sir.

649
00:45:55,090 --> 00:45:57,259
I don't toss people out right away.

650
00:45:58,177 --> 00:45:59,887
I give them three chances.

651
00:45:59,970 --> 00:46:03,348
But you betrayed my granddaughter,

652
00:46:03,432 --> 00:46:08,729
bugged my room,
and tried to ruin this deal.

653
00:46:09,605 --> 00:46:11,648
That's three strikes already.

654
00:46:11,732 --> 00:46:13,567
-Sir…
-Get out.

655
00:46:40,427 --> 00:46:41,512
Is this broken?

656
00:46:42,221 --> 00:46:43,055
Please.

657
00:46:43,138 --> 00:46:44,264
Thank you.

658
00:46:53,148 --> 00:46:54,149
INVALID ID

659
00:47:00,364 --> 00:47:02,699
Sir, you need to come out.

660
00:47:06,745 --> 00:47:08,080
Mr. Baek Hyun-woo.

661
00:47:08,163 --> 00:47:09,957
Please leave your ID card,
corporate phone,

662
00:47:10,040 --> 00:47:13,293
laptop, and other equipment behind
and leave the building.

663
00:47:13,377 --> 00:47:16,129
It's past working hours.
You can't do this out of the blue.

664
00:47:16,213 --> 00:47:18,048
It's the chairman's orders.

665
00:47:18,131 --> 00:47:18,966
Please leave.

666
00:47:19,049 --> 00:47:21,260
Does the Security Team have no rules?

667
00:47:26,014 --> 00:47:28,308
Are you the chairman's men or something?

668
00:47:29,476 --> 00:47:31,603
It's past working hours. Go home.

669
00:47:32,646 --> 00:47:34,690
But the chairman ordered us--

670
00:47:34,773 --> 00:47:36,483
Just go home.

671
00:47:42,447 --> 00:47:43,532
At least make a deal.

672
00:47:44,157 --> 00:47:46,410
Demand something in return for quitting.

673
00:47:46,493 --> 00:47:48,579
Will you really let them kick you out?

674
00:47:48,662 --> 00:47:49,580
They can't.

675
00:47:50,247 --> 00:47:55,752
The chairman can fire me as a director,
but I'm also a team manager.

676
00:47:55,836 --> 00:47:58,380
He needs a legitimate reason to fire one.

677
00:47:58,463 --> 00:48:02,217
I know the Audit Team
couldn't find any reason to fire me.

678
00:48:02,843 --> 00:48:03,677
That's…

679
00:48:05,220 --> 00:48:07,222
Fine, but why are you still here?

680
00:48:08,223 --> 00:48:11,518
You were so eager for a divorce
that you secretly prepared for it.

681
00:48:12,227 --> 00:48:15,105
So why are you still here
and letting them humiliate you?

682
00:48:15,188 --> 00:48:16,231
When you were with me…

683
00:48:19,401 --> 00:48:20,903
You had to put up with it.

684
00:48:21,528 --> 00:48:22,529
But not anymore.

685
00:48:23,697 --> 00:48:24,531
I know.

686
00:48:25,115 --> 00:48:28,368
I'm only doing this
because I still want to be here.

687
00:48:36,001 --> 00:48:37,002
How are you feeling?

688
00:48:38,962 --> 00:48:40,047
I'm okay.

689
00:49:10,744 --> 00:49:14,456
-Ms. Hong.
-You better get in, or I'll run you over.

690
00:49:37,354 --> 00:49:38,772
Which one was it?

691
00:49:38,855 --> 00:49:40,607
The company? A reunion? A bar?

692
00:49:41,692 --> 00:49:44,653
Don't bother denying it.

693
00:49:44,736 --> 00:49:46,613
I know everything about divorce.

694
00:49:48,365 --> 00:49:49,491
There's only one answer.

695
00:49:50,158 --> 00:49:50,993
A mistress.

696
00:49:53,787 --> 00:49:54,746
Ma'am…

697
00:49:55,956 --> 00:49:57,582
Hae-in was the only woman in my life.

698
00:49:57,666 --> 00:49:59,793
Then don't go!

699
00:49:59,876 --> 00:50:02,879
You're all she has,
so why are you leaving?

700
00:50:02,963 --> 00:50:04,131
I'm not going anywhere.

701
00:50:06,258 --> 00:50:07,759
How could I possibly leave her?

702
00:50:09,052 --> 00:50:11,096
That's why I'm still at the company.

703
00:50:11,179 --> 00:50:12,389
I'll stay by her side

704
00:50:13,265 --> 00:50:14,641
at all costs.

705
00:50:15,350 --> 00:50:16,184
Also…

706
00:50:17,352 --> 00:50:22,149
I'll get to the bottom
of who bugged the chairman's room,

707
00:50:22,232 --> 00:50:24,818
handed the recording to Apollon,

708
00:50:24,901 --> 00:50:26,445
and wanted me out of the family.

709
00:50:33,535 --> 00:50:34,369
About that…

710
00:50:36,455 --> 00:50:38,290
I do have my suspicions.

711
00:50:38,373 --> 00:50:39,332
Ms. Moh?

712
00:50:40,292 --> 00:50:41,126
How did you know?

713
00:50:41,209 --> 00:50:43,295
Everyone knows how much you despise her.

714
00:50:44,129 --> 00:50:45,130
That's not why.

715
00:50:45,756 --> 00:50:48,050
She's scarier than you think.

716
00:50:48,133 --> 00:50:51,470
She's been living under a false identity
and deceiving us for decades.

717
00:50:52,304 --> 00:50:53,972
What do you mean?

718
00:50:55,223 --> 00:50:57,309
Her real name is Oh Sun-yeong.

719
00:50:57,893 --> 00:50:59,478
She had a son,

720
00:50:59,561 --> 00:51:01,229
and he's 34 years old now.

721
00:51:01,313 --> 00:51:03,857
And Oh Sun-yeong is deceased on paper.

722
00:51:04,983 --> 00:51:07,194
So? Insane, isn't it?

723
00:51:07,277 --> 00:51:09,071
Don't you want to team up with me?

724
00:51:09,154 --> 00:51:11,323
I even have a partner named Conan.

725
00:51:15,702 --> 00:51:17,496
Iced Americano all the way, right?

726
00:51:17,579 --> 00:51:20,999
-How did you know?
-I can see that you're the stubborn type.

727
00:51:21,083 --> 00:51:22,417
I see.

728
00:51:22,501 --> 00:51:25,420
He could pass as a shaman.

729
00:51:25,504 --> 00:51:26,797
I practically raised him myself.

730
00:51:26,880 --> 00:51:28,256
What have you found out?

731
00:51:28,340 --> 00:51:31,218
I met with the guard
from Oh Sun-yeong's penitentiary.

732
00:51:31,301 --> 00:51:32,552
She gave birth behind bars

733
00:51:32,636 --> 00:51:34,971
and sent him
to an orphanage in Gangwon Province.

734
00:51:35,055 --> 00:51:36,306
-Where exactly?
-It's…

735
00:51:38,767 --> 00:51:41,895
-Wonsan.
-Isn't that near the hunting ground?

736
00:51:41,978 --> 00:51:43,480
Yes, our villa is there.

737
00:51:43,563 --> 00:51:45,398
Yes, it's very close.

738
00:51:45,482 --> 00:51:47,192
It's Evergreen Hope Orphanage.

739
00:51:47,818 --> 00:51:48,652
"Evergreen"?

740
00:51:49,277 --> 00:51:50,403
That's--

741
00:51:50,904 --> 00:51:53,156
My father and that wench sponsored

742
00:51:53,240 --> 00:51:55,742
and gave out scholarships there
up until a decade ago!

743
00:52:00,122 --> 00:52:03,416
That orphanage
went up in flames ten years ago.

744
00:52:03,500 --> 00:52:05,544
I believe the director passed away too.

745
00:52:05,627 --> 00:52:08,130
Do you know anyone we could reach out to?

746
00:52:09,005 --> 00:52:10,674
-I'm not sure.
-What about him?

747
00:52:10,757 --> 00:52:11,716
Who?

748
00:52:11,800 --> 00:52:14,010
The man who came
to the hunting ground with you.

749
00:52:14,636 --> 00:52:16,471
The one who wanted to buy our dog.

750
00:52:16,555 --> 00:52:18,932
-Mr. Yoon Eun-sung?
-Don't be absurd.

751
00:52:19,015 --> 00:52:21,143
What? You said he looked familiar too.

752
00:52:22,936 --> 00:52:25,230
Whom did he remind you of?

753
00:52:26,022 --> 00:52:28,942
There was this boy at the orphanage.

754
00:52:29,025 --> 00:52:31,862
He was so smart that he received
scholarships from Queens Group.

755
00:52:31,945 --> 00:52:34,447
But he was taken
to the police station once

756
00:52:34,531 --> 00:52:36,324
after poisoning and killing
a neighbor's dog.

757
00:52:36,408 --> 00:52:38,285
And Mr. Yoon looked like him.

758
00:52:40,871 --> 00:52:43,165
He did say he was adopted to the U.S.

759
00:52:43,248 --> 00:52:46,168
That's right. That boy
was adopted to the U.S. as well.

760
00:52:50,672 --> 00:52:52,424
Isn't she the chairman's mistress?

761
00:52:52,507 --> 00:52:54,968
It's a men's watch.
I wonder whom she gifted it to.

762
00:52:55,051 --> 00:52:56,678
She's scarier than you think.

763
00:52:56,761 --> 00:53:00,056
She's been living under a false identity
and deceiving us for decades.

764
00:53:00,140 --> 00:53:03,393
She gave birth behind bars and sent him
to an orphanage in Gangwon Province.

765
00:53:03,476 --> 00:53:04,769
I was adopted overseas.

766
00:53:04,853 --> 00:53:06,605
He was adopted by a Korean family at 12.

767
00:53:06,688 --> 00:53:09,316
She had a son, and he's 34 years old now.

768
00:53:09,399 --> 00:53:11,359
So I have no family now.

769
00:53:19,659 --> 00:53:21,828
POWER OF ATTORNEY
HONG MAN-DAE

770
00:53:24,915 --> 00:53:26,416
RIGHT TO MAKE ANY MEDICAL DECISIONS

771
00:53:28,418 --> 00:53:29,836
Why are you signing this?

772
00:53:30,462 --> 00:53:33,256
Why would you give me
the right to make decisions for you?

773
00:53:33,340 --> 00:53:35,842
When the prosecution investigates
the secret fund,

774
00:53:35,926 --> 00:53:38,011
they might not be convinced
that you embezzled it

775
00:53:38,094 --> 00:53:40,847
just because you have some
of the money under your name.

776
00:53:40,931 --> 00:53:44,059
Anyone could be the financial manager.

777
00:53:44,142 --> 00:53:45,268
Is that so?

778
00:53:46,853 --> 00:53:48,021
See?

779
00:53:48,813 --> 00:53:50,065
This is for my sake.

780
00:53:50,148 --> 00:53:51,775
Will you still not do it?

781
00:53:53,401 --> 00:53:54,444
No, I should.

782
00:53:54,527 --> 00:53:58,531
Today is your birthday,
so this could be my gift to you.

783
00:53:58,615 --> 00:53:59,658
Right.

784
00:53:59,741 --> 00:54:02,369
Yes, I'll consider it my birthday gift.

785
00:54:16,299 --> 00:54:19,678
AUTHORIZER
HONG MAN-DAE

786
00:54:33,483 --> 00:54:36,319
Wait, why is Mr. Yoon sitting here?

787
00:54:36,403 --> 00:54:38,196
He should sit with us.

788
00:54:38,280 --> 00:54:39,948
Well…

789
00:54:40,031 --> 00:54:41,157
It was my order.

790
00:54:41,783 --> 00:54:42,659
What?

791
00:54:42,742 --> 00:54:45,120
It's only right. He's not family anyway.

792
00:54:46,705 --> 00:54:49,749
Why? You sit with us
when you're not family either.

793
00:54:51,501 --> 00:54:52,627
So?

794
00:54:53,336 --> 00:54:56,298
So you can be family
even if it's not on paper.

795
00:54:56,381 --> 00:54:58,174
-If you live together--
-So?

796
00:54:59,301 --> 00:55:01,261
You're saying Mr. Yoon
could become family?

797
00:55:01,344 --> 00:55:02,345
Is that what you think?

798
00:55:03,972 --> 00:55:05,724
No, I never said that.

799
00:55:06,933 --> 00:55:08,768
Hae-in got divorced not too long ago.

800
00:55:08,852 --> 00:55:12,063
What would people think
if he sat next to her?

801
00:55:12,147 --> 00:55:14,357
They'd think she has shallow intentions.

802
00:55:15,734 --> 00:55:17,110
"Shallow"?

803
00:55:17,193 --> 00:55:19,195
Did you seriously just say that?

804
00:55:19,279 --> 00:55:20,363
Really?

805
00:55:20,447 --> 00:55:21,281
Then,

806
00:55:22,032 --> 00:55:24,034
you shouldn't give them wrong ideas.

807
00:55:24,117 --> 00:55:26,411
Who are you to order people around?

808
00:55:29,372 --> 00:55:30,665
Seon-hwa

809
00:55:31,291 --> 00:55:32,417
is the lady of the house.

810
00:55:35,003 --> 00:55:37,255
You're really something, you know?

811
00:55:40,300 --> 00:55:41,509
All right.

812
00:55:41,593 --> 00:55:45,096
Let's not get upset over nothing
on this good day.

813
00:55:54,689 --> 00:55:56,191
Why does she have this?

814
00:55:56,274 --> 00:55:59,235
This was Mom's!

815
00:55:59,319 --> 00:56:01,196
She wore it all her life,

816
00:56:01,279 --> 00:56:03,073
and I was supposed to inherit it.

817
00:56:03,156 --> 00:56:05,909
So how could you give it to her?

818
00:56:05,992 --> 00:56:08,870
Okay. Let me go, and I'll take it off.

819
00:56:10,622 --> 00:56:14,209
Father, why have you gone crazy?

820
00:56:14,292 --> 00:56:17,670
You may have always been a workaholic,
but you weren't like this.

821
00:56:17,754 --> 00:56:19,631
Why can't you make good judgment?

822
00:56:19,714 --> 00:56:22,550
Look who's talking! How dare you?

823
00:56:23,176 --> 00:56:26,179
You've kicked Beom-seok out
and treat Beom-jun like an idiot.

824
00:56:26,262 --> 00:56:28,556
Look who's left now.

825
00:56:28,640 --> 00:56:32,394
You only have this bitch
who's waiting to milk you dry!

826
00:56:32,477 --> 00:56:33,603
Watch what you say!

827
00:56:33,686 --> 00:56:37,023
When my children backed out in fear
that I'd send them to jail,

828
00:56:37,107 --> 00:56:38,942
she was the only one who stepped up!

829
00:56:39,025 --> 00:56:42,695
Maybe she's not afraid to go
since she's been there before!

830
00:56:42,779 --> 00:56:44,239
What nonsense are you spewing?

831
00:56:45,407 --> 00:56:46,533
You know nothing.

832
00:56:46,616 --> 00:56:48,910
I was going to tell you later.

833
00:56:48,993 --> 00:56:51,413
She's been to prison

834
00:56:51,496 --> 00:56:53,164
and even had a child!

835
00:56:53,248 --> 00:56:56,042
She's been living
under a false name all along!

836
00:56:57,085 --> 00:56:59,838
Beom-ja, why are you so mean to me?

837
00:57:00,380 --> 00:57:02,507
I may have been poor,

838
00:57:03,091 --> 00:57:05,802
but I've always strived
to live an honest life.

839
00:57:09,347 --> 00:57:11,558
I'm sorry, sir.

840
00:57:13,184 --> 00:57:14,769
I can't do this anymore.

841
00:57:15,520 --> 00:57:17,439
I'll leave this house.

842
00:57:18,731 --> 00:57:20,442
Come on.

843
00:57:21,359 --> 00:57:24,154
You know Beom-ja always talks nonsense.

844
00:57:24,863 --> 00:57:25,780
You little brat!

845
00:57:25,864 --> 00:57:29,075
You better stop, or I'll send you
to a mental asylum. Got it?

846
00:57:29,159 --> 00:57:30,326
A mental asylum?

847
00:57:32,579 --> 00:57:34,789
Then I ought to do this much.

848
00:57:37,584 --> 00:57:39,294
You!

849
00:57:39,961 --> 00:57:41,087
Let her go!

850
00:57:41,171 --> 00:57:43,465
I said, let her go!

851
00:57:52,640 --> 00:57:53,475
Father…

852
00:57:53,558 --> 00:57:54,642
I'm so sick of you.

853
00:57:54,726 --> 00:57:57,770
Your mom got her revenge on me

854
00:57:57,854 --> 00:57:59,606
by giving birth to you.

855
00:57:59,689 --> 00:58:03,818
How could you torment me to this day?

856
00:58:03,902 --> 00:58:05,737
Just leave, will you?

857
00:58:05,820 --> 00:58:06,988
Leave, I beg you.

858
00:58:07,071 --> 00:58:08,406
Just go!

859
00:58:17,790 --> 00:58:18,708
I'll do that.

860
00:58:19,542 --> 00:58:22,086
You won't be able to save face

861
00:58:22,170 --> 00:58:24,380
after kicking out two of your three kids.

862
00:58:24,464 --> 00:58:25,965
I'm leaving of my own will.

863
00:58:27,217 --> 00:58:29,385
Have a great birthday party today.

864
00:58:32,013 --> 00:58:34,057
I'll at least attend your funeral.

865
00:58:34,140 --> 00:58:35,183
Even still,

866
00:58:35,808 --> 00:58:37,894
I hope you live a long life.

867
00:58:46,653 --> 00:58:47,987
That little…

868
00:58:56,371 --> 00:58:57,413
It's okay.

869
00:58:58,915 --> 00:59:00,291
All right, now.

870
00:59:02,293 --> 00:59:04,295
Are the hair follicles intact?

871
00:59:04,379 --> 00:59:06,839
Probably. I pulled them out
with all my might.

872
00:59:07,924 --> 00:59:08,925
And Mr. Yoon's?

873
00:59:13,388 --> 00:59:14,222
Thank you.

874
00:59:21,271 --> 00:59:22,272
Ma'am.

875
00:59:31,114 --> 00:59:32,323
Are you okay?

876
00:59:34,534 --> 00:59:35,827
No…

877
00:59:36,578 --> 00:59:39,455
I'm not okay, Hyun-woo…

878
00:59:40,164 --> 00:59:44,294
My father hit me
for the first time in his life.

879
00:59:45,044 --> 00:59:49,132
He hit me…

880
01:00:00,476 --> 01:00:02,395
What if Grandfather faints

881
01:00:02,478 --> 01:00:05,064
due to happiness
after receiving my surprise?

882
01:00:05,148 --> 01:00:06,983
Don't push yourself too much. Be calm.

883
01:00:07,066 --> 01:00:09,027
I've been way too calm all along.

884
01:00:09,110 --> 01:00:10,862
I need to change.

885
01:00:10,945 --> 01:00:12,780
Can't you see? I'm Queens' solution now.

886
01:00:12,864 --> 01:00:15,325
I'm their lifesaver.

887
01:00:17,619 --> 01:00:21,831
Still, your grandfather wants
a quiet birthday this year.

888
01:00:21,914 --> 01:00:24,250
You're so innocent.

889
01:00:24,334 --> 01:00:26,002
Don't let him fool you. It's just a test.

890
01:00:26,085 --> 01:00:28,421
It's like midterms or exams.

891
01:00:28,504 --> 01:00:31,299
In that aspect, this is like the CSAT.

892
01:00:31,382 --> 01:00:34,969
Will I be chosen as the heir or not?

893
01:00:35,720 --> 01:00:36,679
It's the play-off.

894
01:00:36,763 --> 01:00:37,972
But I have a hunch.

895
01:00:39,557 --> 01:00:40,683
What? What kind?

896
01:00:43,895 --> 01:00:44,896
That today will be

897
01:00:45,605 --> 01:00:48,149
the best day of my life.

898
01:00:49,108 --> 01:00:49,942
I see.

899
01:00:50,693 --> 01:00:51,903
Wear a pretty dress

900
01:00:51,986 --> 01:00:53,613
and take Geon-u to the hair salon.

901
01:00:55,365 --> 01:00:56,741
I'll be waiting.

902
01:01:06,209 --> 01:01:07,043
Honey.

903
01:01:11,422 --> 01:01:12,256
Thank you.

904
01:01:31,067 --> 01:01:31,901
You fool.

905
01:01:31,984 --> 01:01:34,404
CONGRATULATIONS
ON CHAIRMAN HONG'S FOURTH 20TH BIRTHDAY!

906
01:01:58,219 --> 01:02:02,974
CHAIRMAN HONG'S 80TH BIRTHDAY

907
01:02:18,156 --> 01:02:22,827
We've gathered together
to celebrate the chairman's birthday.

908
01:02:23,578 --> 01:02:24,787
Our family went through

909
01:02:25,455 --> 01:02:27,373
a rough patch recently.

910
01:02:27,457 --> 01:02:31,377
People slandered him and spread rumors.

911
01:02:32,503 --> 01:02:33,671
However,

912
01:02:33,755 --> 01:02:35,965
our hero neither gave in

913
01:02:36,048 --> 01:02:37,175
nor gave up.

914
01:02:37,258 --> 01:02:40,219
He overcame all the hardships.

915
01:02:40,303 --> 01:02:42,847
Everyone, please clap
for Chairman Hong Man-dae.

916
01:03:09,040 --> 01:03:10,625
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

917
01:03:41,697 --> 01:03:42,573
POWER OFF

918
01:03:53,584 --> 01:03:55,545
Dreams come true.

919
01:03:55,628 --> 01:03:59,423
There's Mickey Mouse in the U.S.
and Totoro in Japan.

920
01:03:59,507 --> 01:04:02,134
Queens Amusement Park,
which will be the biggest one

921
01:04:02,218 --> 01:04:04,053
in Northeast Asia,

922
01:04:04,136 --> 01:04:06,889
also has a beloved character.

923
01:04:06,973 --> 01:04:09,767
I created it myself.

924
01:04:09,851 --> 01:04:13,354
It's Chairman Hong, my grandfather.

925
01:04:14,063 --> 01:04:15,231
Me?

926
01:04:17,608 --> 01:04:20,528
Soo-cheol prepared
a great birthday gift for Father.

927
01:04:20,611 --> 01:04:21,612
You're right.

928
01:04:22,655 --> 01:04:24,740
I'm ecstatic to finally be able

929
01:04:24,824 --> 01:04:27,493
to reveal it to you all.

930
01:04:30,037 --> 01:04:31,873
Come on out, Man-sung!

931
01:04:53,436 --> 01:04:55,521
We're planning to sell
this Man-sung merchandise

932
01:04:55,605 --> 01:04:57,732
as toys, golf wear, mugs,

933
01:04:57,815 --> 01:05:01,694
keychains, mats, and more.

934
01:05:01,777 --> 01:05:02,737
And, of course,

935
01:05:03,738 --> 01:05:05,990
we'll issue NFTs as well.

936
01:05:14,582 --> 01:05:16,709
Tell Soo-cheol to stop.

937
01:05:20,338 --> 01:05:22,757
Please stop.

938
01:05:30,640 --> 01:05:33,142
CHEON DA-HYE

939
01:05:40,900 --> 01:05:42,944
I got the DNA results.

940
01:05:57,208 --> 01:05:58,209
Da-hye.

941
01:06:09,887 --> 01:06:10,846
Honey.

942
01:06:56,976 --> 01:06:58,227
Da…

943
01:06:58,310 --> 01:06:59,311
Da-hye.

944
01:07:11,490 --> 01:07:12,533
Da-hye.

945
01:07:14,910 --> 01:07:15,995
Da-hye!

946
01:07:36,348 --> 01:07:37,308
Da-hye.

947
01:07:55,910 --> 01:07:57,369
Da-hye!

948
01:07:57,453 --> 01:07:59,121
Geon-u!

949
01:08:05,336 --> 01:08:08,923
My son can't go to bed
if I don't tuck him in.

950
01:08:10,591 --> 01:08:12,718
Please, Da-hye!

951
01:08:19,850 --> 01:08:21,894
Geon-u.

952
01:08:21,977 --> 01:08:22,895
Let's try some.

953
01:08:22,978 --> 01:08:24,396
Just one bite, Geon-u.

954
01:08:28,359 --> 01:08:29,193
What's wrong?

955
01:08:34,240 --> 01:08:35,116
Geon-u.

956
01:08:37,159 --> 01:08:39,411
Geon-u.

957
01:08:40,871 --> 01:08:41,914
Geon-u.

958
01:08:42,998 --> 01:08:44,125
Mommy's here.

959
01:09:02,810 --> 01:09:03,769
BEOM-JA

960
01:09:18,742 --> 01:09:19,952
HYUN-WOO

961
01:09:26,458 --> 01:09:29,336
Why are you calling me at this hour?

962
01:09:29,420 --> 01:09:31,172
I'm sorry. It's urgent.

963
01:09:31,255 --> 01:09:32,798
Are you alone, sir?

964
01:09:32,882 --> 01:09:34,508
I'm playing Janggi. Why?

965
01:09:34,592 --> 01:09:36,802
Please just listen if Ms. Moh is with you.

966
01:09:36,886 --> 01:09:38,053
What?

967
01:09:40,389 --> 01:09:43,225
I did a DNA test on Ms. Moh and Mr. Yoon.

968
01:09:43,309 --> 01:09:46,020
There's a 99% chance or higher
that they're related.

969
01:09:46,812 --> 01:09:49,481
Mr. Yoon has been gathering your shares.

970
01:09:49,565 --> 01:09:52,985
He has already taken 9.6%
of the directors' shares

971
01:09:53,068 --> 01:09:55,362
through a foreclosure agreement.

972
01:09:55,446 --> 01:09:58,741
Sir, you must withdraw
the convertible rights now.

973
01:10:00,451 --> 01:10:01,994
All right.

974
01:10:04,288 --> 01:10:06,040
I'll call you back later.

975
01:10:13,589 --> 01:10:14,673
Checkmate.

976
01:10:18,385 --> 01:10:19,303
I got the king.

977
01:10:28,312 --> 01:10:31,482
What's the matter?
Do you have something to say?

978
01:10:36,904 --> 01:10:37,780
You…

979
01:10:40,532 --> 01:10:41,533
Goodness.

980
01:10:42,660 --> 01:10:44,036
Are you okay?

981
01:10:53,087 --> 01:10:55,839
No, you're probably not okay.

982
01:10:55,923 --> 01:10:57,258
That's what the drug does.

983
01:10:57,841 --> 01:11:02,346
Ten minutes in the respiratory system,
and you'll slowly become paralyzed.

984
01:11:02,429 --> 01:11:03,889
So it was true.

985
01:11:04,848 --> 01:11:05,683
How incredible.

986
01:11:13,649 --> 01:11:14,942
Don't worry.

987
01:11:15,734 --> 01:11:17,027
You won't die right away.

988
01:11:21,156 --> 01:11:24,243
If you do, this will be useless.

989
01:11:24,326 --> 01:11:27,538
I can only become your legal guardian

990
01:11:27,621 --> 01:11:31,959
and have a say if you're in a coma.

991
01:11:32,042 --> 01:11:33,002
So…

992
01:11:33,711 --> 01:11:34,795
be in a coma

993
01:11:34,878 --> 01:11:37,256
for two to three months before you die.

994
01:11:39,258 --> 01:11:40,676
Can you do that for me?

995
01:12:08,203 --> 01:12:09,330
See?

996
01:12:09,413 --> 01:12:12,541
Hyun-woo and Beom-ja were right.

997
01:12:13,500 --> 01:12:16,670
So why did you trust me instead of them?

998
01:12:29,683 --> 01:12:35,397
-Happy birthday to you
-Happy birthday to you

999
01:12:36,231 --> 01:12:39,860
-Happy birthday, dear Beom-ja
-Happy birthday, dear Beom-ja

1000
01:12:39,943 --> 01:12:42,654
-Happy birthday to you
-Happy birthday to you

1001
01:12:42,738 --> 01:12:43,572
Come here.

1002
01:12:49,703 --> 01:12:51,413
I'll take it now. Please smile.

1003
01:12:53,791 --> 01:12:55,542
Say cheese on the count of three.

1004
01:12:55,626 --> 01:12:59,296
Okay. One, two, three.

1005
01:12:59,380 --> 01:13:00,297
Cheese.

1006
01:13:13,811 --> 01:13:16,271
What's with you guys?
Don't you know who I am?

1007
01:13:16,355 --> 01:13:18,357
Why can't I see him?

1008
01:13:18,440 --> 01:13:21,693
Only those allowed
by his legal guardian can enter.

1009
01:13:21,777 --> 01:13:23,153
-Move.
-No, sir.

1010
01:13:23,237 --> 01:13:24,947
-No, sir!
-Goodness.

1011
01:13:25,030 --> 01:13:25,864
Hey.

1012
01:13:25,948 --> 01:13:29,701
We're the chairman's children.
So who's this guardian?

1013
01:13:29,785 --> 01:13:31,120
-Move.
-No, ma'am.

1014
01:13:31,203 --> 01:13:32,413
Goodness.

1015
01:13:42,089 --> 01:13:43,006
You bitch.

1016
01:13:43,090 --> 01:13:45,175
What have you done?

1017
01:13:45,759 --> 01:13:47,177
Give me a minute.

1018
01:13:48,095 --> 01:13:49,346
What happened, Attorney Han?

1019
01:13:49,430 --> 01:13:52,766
The chairman had a sudden heart attack
and received treatment.

1020
01:13:53,600 --> 01:13:55,727
But he's currently unconscious.

1021
01:13:55,811 --> 01:13:57,062
No, Father!

1022
01:13:58,439 --> 01:14:03,402
And his current legal guardian
is Ms. Moh Seul-hee.

1023
01:14:07,865 --> 01:14:08,907
What do you mean?

1024
01:14:08,991 --> 01:14:10,200
Right.

1025
01:14:14,079 --> 01:14:17,624
The chairman recently gave
the power of attorney to her.

1026
01:14:17,708 --> 01:14:21,670
According to this document,
Ms. Moh is his legal guardian

1027
01:14:21,753 --> 01:14:25,507
and has the right
to make decisions in his stead

1028
01:14:25,591 --> 01:14:27,634
since he's unconscious right now.

1029
01:14:27,718 --> 01:14:32,014
If this is proven to be fabricated,
you'll be charged with the forgery, use,

1030
01:14:32,097 --> 01:14:34,683
and making of untrue entries
in this official document.

1031
01:14:34,766 --> 01:14:38,228
I have a video of him signing this paper.

1032
01:14:38,312 --> 01:14:39,313
I'll send it to you.

1033
01:14:40,105 --> 01:14:40,981
-I'm dizzy.
-Honey.

1034
01:14:41,064 --> 01:14:42,274
Honey.

1035
01:14:45,819 --> 01:14:49,406
He must've had zero trust in his children
to give me the right to act in his stead

1036
01:14:49,490 --> 01:14:52,117
in case something like this occurred.

1037
01:14:52,201 --> 01:14:55,329
You were only interested
in taking as much money from him

1038
01:14:55,412 --> 01:14:56,872
as possible.

1039
01:14:56,955 --> 01:14:59,500
The chairman chose the company

1040
01:15:00,042 --> 01:15:02,669
he raised his entire life
over his own family.

1041
01:15:02,753 --> 01:15:04,838
I know what he wants more than any of you.

1042
01:15:05,881 --> 01:15:06,965
I'll follow his wishes.

1043
01:15:08,008 --> 01:15:09,468
"His wishes"?

1044
01:15:10,761 --> 01:15:12,137
"His wishes"?

1045
01:15:13,430 --> 01:15:15,641
Hey, I don't know about that.

1046
01:15:16,558 --> 01:15:18,268
But I do know what you want.

1047
01:15:18,352 --> 01:15:20,479
You and your son,
Yoon Eun-sung, are going to use

1048
01:15:20,562 --> 01:15:22,606
the power of attorney to your favor!

1049
01:15:22,689 --> 01:15:23,815
What do you mean?

1050
01:15:25,400 --> 01:15:28,153
Yoon Eun-sung? The Yoon Eun-sung?

1051
01:15:28,237 --> 01:15:29,238
Correct, sir.

1052
01:15:29,321 --> 01:15:30,864
We checked the DNA results.

1053
01:15:34,243 --> 01:15:35,911
Yes, Mr. Yoon is my son.

1054
01:15:35,994 --> 01:15:38,247
Why? Is that wrong?

1055
01:15:38,330 --> 01:15:40,165
Does that change anything?

1056
01:15:41,208 --> 01:15:42,626
Hey!

1057
01:15:42,709 --> 01:15:43,544
Damn it!

1058
01:15:43,627 --> 01:15:45,837
Beom-ja, keep acting cute,

1059
01:15:45,921 --> 01:15:48,173
and I might secretly move
your father to another room

1060
01:15:48,257 --> 01:15:50,592
and not give you the chance
to say goodbye to him.

1061
01:15:51,051 --> 01:15:52,177
Do you not believe me?

1062
01:16:05,232 --> 01:16:07,985
This is an unprecedented incident
in the business industry.

1063
01:16:08,068 --> 01:16:09,695
The stockholders' meeting

1064
01:16:09,778 --> 01:16:12,823
agreed to take the Queens' family's rights
over their own company.

1065
01:16:12,906 --> 01:16:16,451
Pione Investment, an investor
in Queens' new resort complex,

1066
01:16:16,535 --> 01:16:17,828
purchased 14.7%

1067
01:16:17,911 --> 01:16:20,914
of Queens' shares
at the beginning of this month…

1068
01:16:21,123 --> 01:16:23,458
…and announced its participation
in the management.

1069
01:16:23,542 --> 01:16:26,795
Pione then amassed
a total of 24.3% of the shares.

1070
01:16:26,878 --> 01:16:31,133
Once Chairman Hong lost consciousness
due to a sudden heart attack,

1071
01:16:31,216 --> 01:16:33,760
Pione exercised the convertible rights

1072
01:16:33,844 --> 01:16:35,637
and took 6.7% of his shares.

1073
01:16:35,721 --> 01:16:37,097
Now, with a total of 31%,

1074
01:16:37,180 --> 01:16:41,018
they've become
the second largest shareholder.

1075
01:16:41,101 --> 01:16:44,146
Pione then organized
a temporary stockholders' meeting.

1076
01:16:44,229 --> 01:16:46,732
With the power of attorney,
Ms. Moh Seul-hee

1077
01:16:46,815 --> 01:16:49,359
sided with Pione Investment.

1078
01:16:49,443 --> 01:16:52,654
A shocking 68.8% supported
the removal of the Queens' family,

1079
01:16:52,738 --> 01:16:57,409
while only 31.2% were against it.

1080
01:16:57,492 --> 01:17:00,746
The business industry is stunned
by this unprecedented event

1081
01:17:00,829 --> 01:17:03,248
where a conglomerate family
lost their power

1082
01:17:03,332 --> 01:17:06,043
due to opposition from the stockholders.

1083
01:17:07,252 --> 01:17:09,254
HONG HAE-IN

1084
01:17:16,386 --> 01:17:18,847
What'll happen to the family now?

1085
01:17:18,930 --> 01:17:19,806
Who knows?

1086
01:17:19,890 --> 01:17:22,017
Even the reporters
don't know where they are.

1087
01:17:22,100 --> 01:17:24,102
They're neither home nor at a hotel.

1088
01:17:24,186 --> 01:17:26,772
They can't even leave the country
due to the investigation.

1089
01:17:26,855 --> 01:17:29,441
You're right. Where could they be?

1090
01:17:44,164 --> 01:17:45,499
YONGDU-RI SUPERMARKET

1091
01:17:57,678 --> 01:17:58,970
Hey.

1092
01:17:59,471 --> 01:18:02,599
-What are you guys doing here?
-Du-gwan, I'm glad you're here.

1093
01:18:02,683 --> 01:18:04,393
I was going to text you.

1094
01:18:04,476 --> 01:18:05,519
Du-gwan.

1095
01:18:05,602 --> 01:18:07,187
How much are the sausages?

1096
01:18:07,270 --> 01:18:08,689
How did you open the store?

1097
01:18:08,772 --> 01:18:10,691
The passcode is 0070.

1098
01:18:10,774 --> 01:18:12,776
Everyone knows that.

1099
01:18:12,859 --> 01:18:14,361
Jeez.

1100
01:18:14,444 --> 01:18:15,487
I should change it.

1101
01:18:15,570 --> 01:18:18,532
The villagers wanted to pay
their unpaid grocery bills,

1102
01:18:18,615 --> 01:18:20,450
so we're running the place for you.

1103
01:18:20,534 --> 01:18:21,868
Look at this.

1104
01:18:21,952 --> 01:18:24,746
-Here.
-We wrote them all down.

1105
01:18:24,830 --> 01:18:27,833
They never stopped by
when I urged them to,

1106
01:18:27,916 --> 01:18:28,750
so why now?

1107
01:18:28,834 --> 01:18:31,962
I guess they wanted to help
after watching the news.

1108
01:18:39,803 --> 01:18:40,804
You know what?

1109
01:18:40,887 --> 01:18:44,725
It's gloomy today,
so how about some ramyeon and soju?

1110
01:18:44,808 --> 01:18:45,892
Sounds good.

1111
01:18:45,976 --> 01:18:46,977
All right.

1112
01:18:49,730 --> 01:18:50,564
Cheers…

1113
01:18:56,445 --> 01:18:57,446
Here.

1114
01:18:58,155 --> 01:18:59,156
Be careful.

1115
01:19:00,323 --> 01:19:02,159
Gosh, that looks delicious.

1116
01:19:02,242 --> 01:19:03,744
Eat up.

1117
01:19:03,827 --> 01:19:05,412
Du-gwan.

1118
01:19:05,495 --> 01:19:09,082
Why would you close the store
over something trivial?

1119
01:19:09,166 --> 01:19:10,417
I'm disappointed in you.

1120
01:19:12,461 --> 01:19:15,464
Why would you be in hiding?

1121
01:19:15,547 --> 01:19:18,008
Let's be honest. It's not your fault.

1122
01:19:18,091 --> 01:19:20,302
Hyun-woo is to blame.

1123
01:19:20,385 --> 01:19:22,721
Hyun-woo didn't do anything wrong.

1124
01:19:22,804 --> 01:19:23,847
I agree.

1125
01:19:23,930 --> 01:19:25,807
He's just a victim of this great typhoon.

1126
01:19:35,484 --> 01:19:36,568
Du-gwan.

1127
01:19:39,070 --> 01:19:41,281
You should know as a farmer yourself.

1128
01:19:41,364 --> 01:19:45,535
Crops don't grow deep roots
if you plant them in the breeze

1129
01:19:45,619 --> 01:19:46,953
since they don't need them.

1130
01:19:47,037 --> 01:19:52,083
But those planted amid strong winds
are deeply rooted and invincible.

1131
01:19:53,668 --> 01:19:58,548
In that sense,
typhoons can be helpful in life.

1132
01:20:00,091 --> 01:20:03,470
You're like one of those people.

1133
01:20:03,553 --> 01:20:04,721
A philosopher.

1134
01:20:05,263 --> 01:20:06,264
Hey.

1135
01:20:07,015 --> 01:20:11,686
If you like typhoons so much,
you can experience them yourselves.

1136
01:20:11,770 --> 01:20:15,565
It breaks my heart to think that my son

1137
01:20:17,067 --> 01:20:19,653
is all alone in that disaster!

1138
01:20:21,947 --> 01:20:23,323
-Du-gwan--
-Let me be.

1139
01:20:24,741 --> 01:20:26,493
Have some ramyeon too.

1140
01:20:27,744 --> 01:20:28,954
What's that?

1141
01:20:30,330 --> 01:20:31,414
What's with the light?

1142
01:20:33,041 --> 01:20:34,501
Who's here at this hour?

1143
01:20:37,170 --> 01:20:38,672
-What?
-Is that Hyun-woo?

1144
01:20:39,464 --> 01:20:40,632
Who?

1145
01:20:40,715 --> 01:20:41,591
Hyun-woo.

1146
01:20:41,675 --> 01:20:43,426
Hey, Hyun-woo!

1147
01:20:44,427 --> 01:20:46,513
I didn't know you were coming.

1148
01:20:47,222 --> 01:20:49,349
Dad, it was urgent.

1149
01:20:50,225 --> 01:20:51,351
Hey, Hyun-woo.

1150
01:20:51,434 --> 01:20:53,061
Why weren't you picking up?

1151
01:20:53,144 --> 01:20:56,106
Do you not eat well?

1152
01:20:56,189 --> 01:20:57,899
You look terrible.

1153
01:20:57,983 --> 01:20:59,276
Goodness.

1154
01:20:59,359 --> 01:21:00,819
Don't be so distraught.

1155
01:21:00,902 --> 01:21:02,571
I'm glad you left that crazy family.

1156
01:21:02,654 --> 01:21:05,031
Look at what happened to them
after they kicked you out.

1157
01:21:05,115 --> 01:21:07,117
-Karma will always find its way.
-Mi-seon.

1158
01:21:07,200 --> 01:21:08,702
-Hold on--
-You bet.

1159
01:21:08,785 --> 01:21:12,747
I was so relieved to hear
that the damn family was ruined.

1160
01:21:12,831 --> 01:21:14,374
Serves them right!

1161
01:21:14,457 --> 01:21:18,253
Anyway, forget about
that sly fox and live a happy life.

1162
01:21:39,065 --> 01:21:39,900
The sly fox

1163
01:21:40,734 --> 01:21:41,568
is here too.

1164
01:21:43,695 --> 01:21:44,821
I see.

1165
01:21:45,864 --> 01:21:47,490
You're here too.

1166
01:21:49,409 --> 01:21:51,077
It's not just her.

1167
01:22:54,766 --> 01:22:56,267
I know,

1168
01:22:56,351 --> 01:22:58,061
but I wanted that life.

1169
01:22:58,144 --> 01:23:00,647
What do you mean? You wanted that?

1170
01:23:00,730 --> 01:23:02,107
Do you have Stockholm syndrome?

1171
01:23:02,190 --> 01:23:03,733
I don't know.

1172
01:23:03,817 --> 01:23:05,026
I just wanted

1173
01:23:06,236 --> 01:23:08,154
to be by Hae-in's side.

1174
01:23:20,667 --> 01:23:22,460
Thank you.

1175
01:23:22,544 --> 01:23:24,087
Goodness, come again.

1176
01:23:24,170 --> 01:23:25,338
Thank you.

1177
01:23:47,610 --> 01:23:48,445
Goodness.

1178
01:23:49,112 --> 01:23:50,196
Are you okay?

1179
01:23:51,031 --> 01:23:53,033
Why are you crying?

1180
01:24:02,375 --> 01:24:03,376
My husband.

1181
01:24:03,918 --> 01:24:05,128
Yes?

1182
01:24:07,047 --> 01:24:09,049
He wants to be by my side.

1183
01:24:11,301 --> 01:24:13,428
And is that so sad?

1184
01:24:15,889 --> 01:24:17,140
Of course.

1185
01:24:20,226 --> 01:24:22,020
Because hearing that makes me want…

1186
01:24:25,315 --> 01:24:26,941
to live.

1187
01:24:29,069 --> 01:24:31,154
Then live. What's stopping you?

1188
01:24:32,072 --> 01:24:34,657
I'm desperate to live too.

1189
01:24:37,452 --> 01:24:38,620
I want to stay

1190
01:24:39,704 --> 01:24:41,498
by his side.

1191
01:24:45,668 --> 01:24:48,213
Gosh. You're drunk.

1192
01:25:01,643 --> 01:25:03,269
I want to live.

1193
01:25:04,145 --> 01:25:05,355
Desperately.

1194
01:25:16,533 --> 01:25:19,410
QUEEN OF TEARS

1195
01:25:49,691 --> 01:25:51,484
They might get back together?

1196
01:25:51,568 --> 01:25:53,444
Do you have feelings for each other?

1197
01:25:54,571 --> 01:25:56,197
Just drink from the kettle!

1198
01:25:56,281 --> 01:25:58,783
This is the best twist ever
since The Sixth Sense.

1199
01:25:58,867 --> 01:26:01,661
-He looked like Leslie Cheung.
-I heard she's a psychopath.

1200
01:26:03,413 --> 01:26:04,289
What?

1201
01:26:04,372 --> 01:26:06,666
Was he born to love me or something?

1202
01:26:06,749 --> 01:26:08,877
Where is she? Hae-in.

1203
01:26:09,586 --> 01:26:12,297
-Whatever happens to me or my family…
-Hae-in is…

1204
01:26:12,380 --> 01:26:13,840
has nothing to do with you.

1205
01:26:13,923 --> 01:26:15,592
If I can prove it,

1206
01:26:15,675 --> 01:26:18,469
I'm going to use
the same tactic Yoon Eun-sung did.

1207
01:26:24,184 --> 01:26:26,186
Subtitle translation by: Soo-ji Kim
